    {
      "id": "3e814b07907e3877d69a2bbe4e13908956550b5d",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 112,
        "name": "Oleg Drokin",
        "email": "green@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "green"
      },
      "date": "2014-04-05 21:52:58.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nIncorporating this patch into my testing I saw a crash I have never seen before:\n\n<0>[66325.137099] LustreError: 15338:0:(cl_lock.c:1122:cl_use_try()) ASSERTION( result != -38 ) failed: \n<0>[66325.146492] LustreError: 15338:0:(cl_lock.c:1122:cl_use_try()) LBUG\n<4>[66325.147946] Pid: 15338, comm: cat\n<4>[66325.148536] \n<4>[66325.148537] Call Trace:\n<4>[66325.149572]  [<ffffffffa03d88a5>] libcfs_debug_dumpstack+0x55/0x80 [libcfs]\n<4>[66325.150338]  [<ffffffffa03d8ea7>] lbug_with_loc+0x47/0xb0 [libcfs]\n<4>[66325.151084]  [<ffffffffa0e87526>] cl_use_try+0x2a6/0x2e0 [obdclass]\n<4>[66325.151826]  [<ffffffffa0e876bd>] cl_enqueue_try+0x15d/0x300 [obdclass]\n<4>[66325.157991]  [<ffffffffa0e8857f>] cl_enqueue_locked+0x6f/0x1f0 [obdclass]\n<4>[66325.158444]  [<ffffffffa0e891be>] cl_lock_request+0x7e/0x270 [obdclass]\n<4>[66325.158903]  [<ffffffffa0e8e024>] cl_io_lock+0x3c4/0x560 [obdclass]\n<4>[66325.159334]  [<ffffffffa0e8e262>] cl_io_loop+0xa2/0x1b0 [obdclass]\n<4>[66325.159761]  [<ffffffffa0a94a3f>] ll_file_io_generic+0x2af/0x6f0 [lustre]\n<4>[66325.160347]  [<ffffffffa0e7e2b9>] ? cl_env_get+0x29/0x350 [obdclass]\n<4>[66325.161044]  [<ffffffffa0a94fbf>] ll_file_aio_read+0x13f/0x2c0 [lustre]\n<4>[66325.162591]  [<ffffffffa0a9547c>] ll_file_read+0x16c/0x2a0 [lustre]\n<4>[66325.163263]  [<ffffffff81189c95>] vfs_read+0xb5/0x1a0\n<4>[66325.163880]  [<ffffffff81189dd1>] sys_read+0x51/0x90\n<4>[66325.164503]  [<ffffffff8100b0b2>] system_call_fastpath+0x16/0x1b\n<4>[66325.165165] \n<0>[66325.265159] Kernel panic - not syncing: LBUG",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "10948662c8e325ac3cea00f63773b242ebc20e24",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 302,
        "name": "Patrick Farrell",
        "email": "paf@cray.com",
        "username": "paf",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2014-04-06 22:07:48.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: -Code-Review\n\nOleg - \nCray has been seeing that assertion (with similar or exactly the same back trace) since we began running racer on 2.5.1.  We haven't seen it except with racer, so it hasn't been a priority for us.\n\nOf course, this patch may introduce another way to hit it, but we have seen the assertion without this patch.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "9eb89938f8dd1c09dd612009f4d9a5fbd1b144f2",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 112,
        "name": "Oleg Drokin",
        "email": "green@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "green"
      },
      "date": "2014-04-06 22:48:23.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nInteresting. I am running racer myself for quite a while, before 2.5.0 was cut for sure and I have never seen this one.\nI did hit many others including this one that we have patch for here, though.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
